				\begin{document}$$\begin{array}{l}{\mathrm{MAT}}_{{\mathrm{mr}}} = 7.17 + 17.1 \times \left[ {{\mathrm{Ia}}} \right] + 25.9 \, \times \left[ {{\mathrm{Ib}}} \right] + 34.4 \, \times \left[ {{\mathrm{Ic}}} \right]\\ - \, 28.6 \, \times \left[ {{\mathrm{IIa}}} \right]\left( {n = 222,r^2 = 0.68} \right)\end{array}$$\end{document}MATmr=7.17+17.1×Ia+25.9×Ib+34.4×Ic-28.6×IIan=222,r2=0.68where the fractional abundance of Ia, Ib, Ic, and IIa was relative to the sum of all brGDGTs. Owing to the very low concentration of brGDGTs in some samples, MAT were calculated using the three most abundant and omnipresent brGDGTs Ia, IIa, and IIIa, in the form of the Multiple Linear Regression Simple index (MATmrs)42 over the past 130–800 kyrs:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
